ref: Jour: Nuovo Cimento A, Vol.99, Issue.5, p.701 (1988)
title: Nuclear-structure studies of 94,96,98,100Mo from the(t,p)reactions at Et = 12 MeV.

Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE), Aldermaston, United Kingdom

x4codes.hlp: Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE), Aldermaston, United Kingdom

x4freetext: An additional experiment on a target consisting of
naturally occurring molybdenum (natMo) and two other
experiments 92,96Mo(t,t) were also carried out at Et
=12 MeV in order to obtain relevant absolute
differential cross- sections for different Mo(t,p)
momentum analysed using the multiangle spectrograph.
The instrument consists of 24 broad-range magnetic
spectrographs of the Browne-Buechner type and is
arranged to have a common magnetic circuit.
mounted in the focal plane of each channel.
Absolute differential cross-sections for the Mo(t,p)
reactions were derived from  a study of the natMo(t,p)
reaction and from analyses of the 92,96Mo(t,t)
exposures. Absolute cross-sections for the elastic
triton data were obtained  by normalizing the (t,t)
angular distributions to the cross-sections predicted
by the optical-model calculation which produced the
best fit to the experimental data.
